<subSubSection pageNumber="914" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="914">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="914">Note:</emphasis>
This name is invalid because the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Varneria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="914">Varneria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was given no separate generic description. Under Art. 42.1, the names of a genus and a species may not be simultaneously validated by a reference to an earlier description or diagnosis, as occurred here. However, some authors (e.g. Merrill, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="914">Interpret. Rumph. Herb. Amb.</emphasis>
: 486. 1917) have treated this as the basionym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Merrill" authorityName="Merrill" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Gardenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="augusta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="914">G. augusta</emphasis>
(L.) Merrill
</taxonomicName>
, wrongly interpreted as the correct name for the species otherwise known as 
<taxonomicName authority="J. Ellis (1761)" authorityName="J. Ellis" authorityYear="1761" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Gardenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jasminoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="914">G. jasminoides</emphasis>
J. Ellis (1761)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
